==English==
===Etymology===

When the [[Portuguese]] discovered Taiwan, they named it '''[[Formosa]]''', which means ''[[beautiful]]'', from Latin '''[[formosa]]''', from '''[[forma]]''', ''form'' or ''shape'', + adjective suffix '''[[-osus]]''', ''full of'' (cf. English ''shapely'')

===Proper noun===
'''Formosa'''

# The name given to the province of [[Taiwan]] by the [[Portuguese]] colonist in the 16th century.

====Translations====
*Bulgarian: [[Формоза]]
*French: [[Formose]]
*Chinese: [[宝岛]], [[寶島]] (Baodao)
*Swedish: Formosa

